## .NET

- Use the OneOf library for discriminated unions in C# versions without native
  union support

## TypeScript

- Avoid type assertions (`as`, `!`) and user-defined type guards — they are
  usually a code smell. Prefer correcting types at the source (e.g.,
  `satisfies`, narrowing, generics) or schema parsing (e.g., valibot) for
  untyped data like JSON.
- Prefer `undefined` over `null` to reduce cognitive overhead

## Node.js

- Prefer pnpm over npm when the project's package manager is ambiguous

## Python

- Always use `py.exe` on Windows instead of `python.exe` or `python3.exe` directly
